Q7.There are moments in life when we have to make hard choices between our roles as private individuals and as citizens with a sense of national loyalty? Discuss with reference to the story you have just read. This question has to be READ WITH INSIGHT

Q8. Dr Sadao was compelled by his duty as a doctor to help the enemy soldier. What made Hana, his wife, sympathetic to him in the face of open defiance from the domestic staff? This question has to be READ WITH INSIGHT.

Q9. How would you explain the reluctance of the soldier to leave the shelter of the doctor’s home even when he knew he couldn’t stay there without risk to the doctor and himself? This question has to be READ WITH INSIGHT.

Q10. What explains the attitude of the General in the matter of the enemy soldier? Was it human consideration, lack of national loyalty, dereliction of duty or simply self-absorption? This question has to be READ WITH INSIGHT.
Q11. While hatred against a member of the enemy race is justifiable, especially during wartime, what makes a human being rise above narrow prejudices? This question has to be READ WITH INSIGHT.
Q12. Do you think the doctor’s final solution to the problem was the best possible one in the circumstances? This question has to be READ WITH INSIGHT.
Q13. Does the story remind you of ‘Birth’ by A. J. Cronin that you read in ‘Snapshots’ last year? What are the similarities? This question has to be READ WITH INSIGHT.
Q14. Is there any film you have seen or novel you have read with a similar theme? This question has to be READ WITH INSIGHT.
